API Overview:
Web UI Automation - Web Application (Web Browser)
API Automation - Web Services, Micro Services Automation
Mobile Automation

APIs / Web Services / Micro Services :
API - Application Programming Interface

Web Services - When we request something through web and get response back

Amazon - Code (Web Servers, Business Logic, Front-End, DB)
Front-End Application - HTML, CSS, Script
Web Server - Request , Response (Valid/Invalid)

Business Logic will evaluate request 
- Are these valid request?
- What resources asking for?
- Create a response using DB

DB - Collection Data (Images, Text, Prices, Descriptions, Catageroy)

www.amazon.com (Domain - URL)
URL - Unified Resources Locator

Middle Layer / Middleware / Application Layer
- Web Services (Request, Response), Web Server, Business Logic

Two Types of Web Services -
1. SOAP - 5% (Envalop, XML)
2. RESTFull / REST API - 95% (XML, JSON, Header)

Manual Testing tools - Postman, SoapUI, Ready API
Automating Web Services - REST : Rest-Assured (JAVA)
SOAP/REST/UI/Mobile/Performace : Karate Framework (Maven JAVA) Grovy-DSL

